    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-03T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-03T06:00:00-05:00" n="153"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4563: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-03T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 3, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 3—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>206. My telegram No. 204, June 2, 3 p.m.<note n="63" xml:id="d153fn63">Not
                        printed.</note> The formal Argentine request<note n="64" xml:id="d153fn64"
                        >League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>, Special
                        Supplement No. 151, p. 97.</note> for convocation of the Assembly was issued
                    last night. It <pb facs="0216" n="151" xml:id="pg_151"/> refers to the Argentine
                    reservation in the May Council (Consulate’s 168, May 12, 9 p.m.) and to the
                    desirability of democratizing the Council functions and it stresses the
                    necessity for all League members to have an opportunity of considering the
                    problems arising out of the Italian-Ethiopian dispute and of assuming their
                    responsibilities therein. It refers to article 10 of the Covenant and to the
                    “unchanging tradition” of Pan-Americanism and indicating as the purpose for the
                    Assembly the questions of the annexation of Ethiopia and of sanctions.</p>
                <p>I understand <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> correspondent has cabled
                    textually essential paragraphs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
